article.headline: Maryland 101, UMKC 50
article.story: BISMARCK, N.D. (AP) -- Jordan Englehardt made two free throws with .5 seconds remaining to lift the University of Mary to a 69-67 victory over North Dakota on Saturday. It was the only basket of the game for Englehardt, who finished with six points for the Marauders (4-8). The win was the second straight in the final second for Mary. On Friday, Bill Shettler's 3-pointer as time ran out beat Mayville State 78-75. Eric Erdmann scored 23 points against the Sioux (6-5). He was 9-for-14 from the field and made all four of his free throw attempts. The Marauders were 16-for-16 from the line. Lance Doppler added 14 points. UND got 15 points and seven rebounds from Mark Kruse. The Sioux outrebounded Mary 35-25, but they were just 21-for-32 from the free throw line. Ervin Youmans scored 12 points for the Sioux.
